FBIS3-25202 "drafr028_c_94012" FBIS-AFR-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Renamo's Dhlakama Asks de Klerk for Houses, Vehicles MB0902133894 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 1030 GMT 9 Feb 94 MB0902133894 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] Afonso Dhlakama, Mozambique National Resistance [Renamo] leader, has asked South African President Frederik de Klerk to provide logistical support, including houses and vehicles, to the Renamo provincial delegations. The Renamo leader made this request during his visit to South Africa, during which he also met businessmen in a bid to attract investors to Mozambique.
